    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-04-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-04-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="223" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d223">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Baker</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">San Jóse</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-04-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 27,
                                1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Nicaraguan Government asked Central American Governments to protest
                            against action of England, President of Costa Rica declined, but most
                            generously proposed to contribute fifth of the indemnity. The Nicaraguan
                            Republic refused paying the indemnity. British occupied Corinto this
                            morning. Nicaragua fortifying San Juan del Sur; are moving large number
                            of soldiers hence.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Baker.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
